org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.mongodb.type.impl

Class StringAsObjectIdType

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.type.AbstractStandardBasicType<T>
      • org.hibernate.type.AbstractSingleColumnStandardBasicType<String>
        • org.hibernate.type.StringType
          • org.hibernate.ogm.datastore.mongodb.type.impl.StringAsObjectIdType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, BasicType, DiscriminatorType<String>, IdentifierType<String>, LiteralType<String>, ProcedureParameterExtractionAware<String>, SingleColumnType<String>, StringRepresentableType<String>, Type, XmlRepresentableType<String>

    public class StringAsObjectIdType
extends StringType
    A Hibernate ORM type (i.e. no grid type) used for storing Strings as ObjectId in MongoDB. It is required for users to be able to specify that specific mapping via Type. Internally the mapping is implemented by StringAsObjectIdGridType.
    Author:
    Gunnar Morling
